*DESCRIPTION_START
The peculiar darkness which fills the air here seems to suck the light into
itself, turning it into tiny particles of soot and ash that you can see, but
cannot touch. You cannot even see all the way to the ground from up here, a
mere thirty or so feet above it. What you can see is the top of a tree some
short way to the south, growing in the manor yard below, and the door in
in the projecting side wall of the attic.
*DESCRIPTION_END

