*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls of this small room were once whitewashed and clean, but now they
are yellowed with age and maltreatment. No attempt has been made to maintain
their condition, leaving them stained with old water-drips and leaks, peeling
in a dozen places and bubbled, ready to break, in dozens more. A rack hangs
along one wall, though it looks as though it's not been polished or cleaned
in twenty years or more. You certainly wouldn't want to entrust it with your
own coat or cloak.
*DESCRIPTION_END

